1
00:00:00,006 --> 00:00:03,007
- Today we're stepping into the world of JavaScript.

2
00:00:03,007 --> 00:00:05,000
- That's right, Jasmine.

3
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,003
If we think of our website as a house,

4
00:00:07,003 --> 00:00:10,002
JavaScript is what turns it from a static structure

5
00:00:10,002 --> 00:00:13,006
into a home with lights, doors that open, and much more.

6
00:00:13,006 --> 00:00:17,000
- [Jasmine] So if HTML is the structure of our house

7
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,000
and CSS is the design,

8
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,007
JavaScript is the electricity that powers everything inside.

9
00:00:22,007 --> 00:00:23,007
- Exactly.

10
00:00:23,007 --> 00:00:26,009
JavaScript lets us interact with the elements on the page.

11
00:00:26,009 --> 00:00:29,004
You can think of it as installing smart home devices

12
00:00:29,004 --> 00:00:31,004
that react to your actions.

13
00:00:31,004 --> 00:00:33,003
- With just a few lines of code,

14
00:00:33,003 --> 00:00:36,003
you can make your website respond to user actions.


15
00:00:36,003 --> 00:00:38,008
- It's like turning on a light with a switch.

16
00:00:38,008 --> 00:00:42,000
JavaScript can show or hide information on a webpage,

17
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,002
change colors,

18
00:00:43,002 --> 00:00:46,000
or even create new content dynamically.

19
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,009
- It's what makes the web feel alive.

20
00:00:48,009 --> 00:00:49,008
Without JavaScript,

21
00:00:49,008 --> 00:00:52,003
our house would be dark and unresponsive,

22
00:00:52,003 --> 00:00:55,009
but with it, we can make it welcoming and interactive.

23
00:00:55,009 --> 00:00:57,003
- And the best part?

24
00:00:57,003 --> 00:00:59,000
